    <item>
      <title>about</title>
      <link>https://lucydot.github.io/blog/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 09 May 2017 13:47:56 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://lucydot.github.io/blog/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;My name is Lucy Whalley and I am a PhD student in the &lt;a href=&#34;http://wmd-group.github.io/&#34;&gt;Walsh Materials Design&lt;/a&gt; group at Imperial College London. My research is based around modelling the electronic structure of materials that are used for solar cells. Funding for my research is through the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.cdt-pv.org/&#34;&gt;Centre for Doctoral Training in New and Sustainable Photovoltaics&lt;/a&gt;. I am very happy to have a PhD project which combines my training in solid state physics, enjoyment of programming and interest in renewable energy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before my PhD I trained as a mathematics teacher, with specialism in Post-Compulsory Education and Training. I have worked as a teacher in a variety of settings - prisons, primary schools and cafes. Software Carpentry.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this website contains&amp;hellip;.My education, employment and publication history can be found via &lt;a href=&#34;http://orcid.org/0000-0002-2992-9871&#34;&gt;Orcid&lt;/a&gt;. My code can be found at &lt;a href=&#34;http://github.com/lucydot&#34;&gt;Github&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This website was built using &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io&#34;&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt; with a tweaked version of the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/aubm/hugo-code-editor-theme/&#34;&gt;code editor&lt;/a&gt; theme.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
